PLAN

I want to deploy the site as statically rendered html pages. I want to maximimize page load speed and SEO. To do this, I want to use the Astro framework to import the react site and render each section as an html page.

STEPS

1. Create a new directory ur-astro and initialize it as a new Astro project. It should import the react component from ur-react.
2. Each section of the site should be rendered to an html page. This includes the language slugs and the localized pages under each language path.
3. The connect dialog and interactive components will remain client-side rendered react components embedded within each html page.
4. Apply all performance and SEO optimizations available in Astro.
5. Create a Makefile with the build target that renders the site to the build/<env> dir.
6. We want to build two <env> versions of the site, main and canary. Each will use a different API URL that will be defined in a build config file.
